WEBVTT

00:13.513 --> 00:16.349
Good morning, baby.

00:26.826 --> 00:28.227
[LINE RINGING]

00:28.261 --> 00:29.328
DANIEL:
<i> Good morning, sunshine.</i>

00:29.362 --> 00:31.431
Hey, did you go
to the dealership already?

00:31.964 --> 00:33.566
Uh, no, I'm at the dojo.

00:33.599 --> 00:36.336
I wanna get an early jump
on today's lesson plan.

00:37.804 --> 00:39.972
Right, yeah,
that sounds important.

00:40.005 --> 00:43.142
<i> Are you still coming in?
We have that lunch
with Anoush.</i>

00:43.175 --> 00:44.611
That's today?

00:43.175 --> 00:44.611
<i> Yeah.</i>

00:45.711 --> 00:47.380
Look, Daniel, he isn't happy.

00:47.413 --> 00:50.883
<i> He's been doing a lot for us.
Not to mention getting
punched in the stomach.</i>

00:50.917 --> 00:52.084
All right, no problem.

00:52.118 --> 00:54.053
<i> It's gonna be a light day.
I'll be there.</i>

00:54.086 --> 00:55.955
Don't worry, all right?

00:55.989 --> 00:57.390
I love you.

00:55.989 --> 00:57.390
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

01:03.029 --> 01:04.531
[PUNCHING]

01:09.102 --> 01:13.106
Robby? I guess the early bird
catches the worm...

01:18.077 --> 01:20.112
It's a cute little place
you got here.

01:20.146 --> 01:23.583
You teach karate,
or gardening?

01:24.416 --> 01:25.951
So, this is what it comes to?

01:25.985 --> 01:27.520
Breaking and entering?

01:28.888 --> 01:31.224
I'm just here
to say thank you.

01:31.257 --> 01:33.125
Thank me for what?

01:33.159 --> 01:37.463
Well, taking our weakest
soldiers from our ranks.

01:37.496 --> 01:38.531
That was kind.

01:38.898 --> 01:40.132
Soldiers...

01:40.166 --> 01:41.534
They're kids.

01:42.267 --> 01:44.704
We were all kids, once.

01:44.737 --> 01:48.841
You may think you got
the best of Johnny Lawrence.

01:48.874 --> 01:51.177
But I promise you,

01:51.211 --> 01:53.412
this time,
I won't let him lose.

01:53.446 --> 01:54.914
Lose what?

01:54.948 --> 01:56.449
This isn't war.

01:57.817 --> 01:59.185
Sure it is.

01:59.752 --> 02:01.253
War never ends.

02:01.287 --> 02:05.257
Peace is just the lull
between battles.

02:05.291 --> 02:10.864
Did you really think you can
attack Cobra Kai and there
wouldn't be any consequences?

02:14.567 --> 02:17.470
You better hope that
your students are ready.

02:17.503 --> 02:22.308
Because I promise you,
ours will be.

02:23.876 --> 02:25.311
[CIGAR SIZZLES]

02:27.880 --> 02:29.682
Regards to Mr. Miyagi.

02:38.891 --> 02:40.058
[SLURPING]

02:40.092 --> 02:41.628
[POP MUSIC PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

02:43.930 --> 02:45.765
It's good.

02:45.798 --> 02:47.166
It has fresh acai,

02:47.199 --> 02:49.936
organic kale,
and free trade hemp oil.

02:49.969 --> 02:51.837
Hemp oil?
I mean, this isn't

02:51.870 --> 02:53.005
gonna get me high, is it?

02:53.039 --> 02:54.206
[LAUGHS] I don't think so.

02:54.240 --> 02:56.342
It's supposed to balance
your kinetic energy.

03:00.079 --> 03:02.481
I'm really glad you called.

03:02.514 --> 03:04.551
I missed hanging out
with you.

03:05.918 --> 03:07.754
So, which one
do you like better?

03:08.654 --> 03:10.789
I've been wearing
the white top a lot.

03:10.823 --> 03:11.991
Well, why does it matter?

03:12.024 --> 03:13.593
You're just gonna
get all sweaty.

03:13.626 --> 03:14.961
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

03:14.994 --> 03:18.197
Wait...
Do you have a crush?

03:18.231 --> 03:19.732
[STAMMERS]
I don't have a crush.

03:19.765 --> 03:20.934
Is it Robby?

03:24.136 --> 03:26.539
Oh, my God!

03:27.306 --> 03:29.509
How long
have you guys been...

03:29.542 --> 03:32.412
We haven't.

03:32.845 --> 03:34.147
We almost.

03:34.180 --> 03:35.882
Does Miguel know?

03:36.949 --> 03:38.351
There's nothing to know.

03:40.252 --> 03:41.988
It's crazy.

03:42.021 --> 03:44.089
After last year,
I got back into karate

03:44.123 --> 03:45.625
to get away
from all the drama.

03:46.592 --> 03:48.594
Well, my mom's therapist
always says,

03:48.627 --> 03:50.964
"You can't hide
from your heart."

03:54.033 --> 03:55.501
I think you should wear
the blue one.

03:55.534 --> 03:57.169
It goes with your eyes.

03:57.203 --> 03:58.437
[BOTH GIGGLE]

03:58.471 --> 04:00.306
All right. Now, shoes.

04:02.274 --> 04:04.277
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

04:02.274 --> 04:04.277
[DOORBELL JINGLES]

04:10.416 --> 04:12.485
Hey, Sensei,
I'm sorry about your loss.

04:12.518 --> 04:14.287
Thanks.

04:14.320 --> 04:15.621
So, how was the funeral?

04:15.654 --> 04:17.656
As good as any funeral
can be.

04:17.689 --> 04:18.724
Yeah...

04:18.757 --> 04:20.493
So, how'd it go around here
while I was gone?

04:20.526 --> 04:23.362
Great. I mean,
Sensei Kreese is tough,

04:23.395 --> 04:25.632
but, uh, he knows
what it takes to win.

04:31.204 --> 04:33.806
Who moved my stuff?

04:33.840 --> 04:35.275
What the hell happened here?

04:35.308 --> 04:37.910
JOHN: Well,
I spent some time
organizing the place.

04:37.943 --> 04:41.214
Bills were unpaid
and invoices were backed up.

04:41.247 --> 04:43.382
The military man in me
couldn't resist.

04:43.416 --> 04:46.019
You've been making yourself
right at home, huh?

04:47.053 --> 04:50.322
A buddy of mine
took that photo.

04:50.356 --> 04:52.659
Yeah, it's nice.
I got a class to run.

04:54.126 --> 04:55.227
Everybody get your gis on.

04:55.261 --> 04:57.262
Training starts
in five minutes.

04:57.296 --> 04:58.898
Gis?

04:57.296 --> 04:58.898
What?

05:00.733 --> 05:03.336
JOHNNY: Yeah, what's wrong?

05:00.733 --> 05:03.336
Nothing is wrong.

05:03.369 --> 05:05.137
I just thought
we were going to the woods

05:05.171 --> 05:07.540
for a special training
today.

05:07.573 --> 05:09.074
What's happening
in the woods?

05:09.108 --> 05:12.745
I thought it was a good time
to separate the men
from the boys.

05:14.046 --> 05:15.848
And the girls, too,
I suppose.

05:15.881 --> 05:18.785
How?

05:15.881 --> 05:18.785
Coyote Creek.

05:20.085 --> 05:21.354
[SIGHS]

05:22.888 --> 05:26.525
I'm not sure
they're ready for that.

05:26.559 --> 05:28.728
There's only one way
to find out.

05:29.896 --> 05:31.230
ELI: We're ready, Sensei.

05:31.264 --> 05:32.965
We want to prove ourselves.

05:35.067 --> 05:36.802
It's up to Sensei Lawrence.

05:36.835 --> 05:40.940
If he says it's okay,
then, and only then,
is it okay.

05:45.811 --> 05:48.414
All right,
what are you waiting for?
Let's go.

05:51.350 --> 05:52.885
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

05:55.788 --> 05:57.657
[ALL PANTING]

06:01.693 --> 06:03.129
Oh, God!

06:03.162 --> 06:04.696
It's so hot out.

06:04.730 --> 06:09.569
I'm sweating in places
I didn't even know
I had pores. [GRUNTS]

06:11.470 --> 06:14.907
[SIGHS] What have I
gotten them into?

06:20.479 --> 06:22.448
All right, guys.
Get out from
under that tree.

06:22.481 --> 06:24.083
It's time to get to work.

06:24.117 --> 06:25.717
[ALL GROANING]

06:25.751 --> 06:28.220
Hey, Mr. LaRusso,
it's like 100 degrees out.

06:28.253 --> 06:29.755
Can we take it easy
today?

06:29.789 --> 06:31.023
Are you kidding?

06:31.056 --> 06:33.392
This heatwave is a gift.

06:33.426 --> 06:36.763
Today, you are going to
experience Shochu-Geiko.

06:37.496 --> 06:39.265
Like the car insurance?

06:39.298 --> 06:41.200
Shochu-Geiko
is a Japanese exercise

06:41.233 --> 06:44.603
where you train
during the hottest days
of the year.

06:44.637 --> 06:46.805
It's about pushing yourself
to your limit.

06:46.839 --> 06:49.575
The fight isn't always
going to come when it's
75 degrees and breezy.

06:49.608 --> 06:52.678
Aren't we supposed
to avoid fighting?

06:52.712 --> 06:57.416
Sometimes, you can't.
Someday, the fight
may come to you.

06:57.450 --> 06:59.118
And I wanna make sure
you're ready.

06:59.152 --> 07:02.655
So, today, we're gonna see
what Miyagi-Do is made of.

07:13.398 --> 07:16.669
Gentlemen, ladies.

07:17.202 --> 07:20.206
Welcome to Coyote Creek.

07:20.239 --> 07:22.208
You've been split
into two teams.

07:22.241 --> 07:24.143
Red...

07:25.377 --> 07:26.912
And black.

07:26.945 --> 07:30.249
The goal is to capture as
many headbands as possible

07:30.282 --> 07:31.684
from the other side.

07:33.019 --> 07:37.023
Today, the people across
from you are not your friends.

07:40.292 --> 07:42.895
They're not your brothers.

07:45.031 --> 07:46.632
They are the enemy.

07:50.302 --> 07:53.873
The last team
standing wins.

07:53.906 --> 07:57.442
How do we get the headbands?

07:53.906 --> 07:57.442
By any means possible.

07:57.476 --> 07:58.744
No rules.

07:58.777 --> 08:01.514
Use your judgement.
This is just
a training exercise.

08:01.547 --> 08:05.718
Correct, but remember,
this is your life.

08:05.751 --> 08:10.088
You lose it, you die.

08:10.122 --> 08:13.358
Hey, guys, sorry I'm late.

08:13.392 --> 08:15.628
Traffic on the 118
was a real bitch.

08:15.661 --> 08:17.262
Put Coyote Creek into the nav.

08:17.296 --> 08:20.899
Nothing came up.

08:17.296 --> 08:20.899
What have you done
to yourself?

08:20.933 --> 08:22.134
Oh, the...

08:22.167 --> 08:25.137
Yeah, you know what,
I just decided
to flip the script,

08:25.170 --> 08:26.706
Hawk-style.

08:27.239 --> 08:29.675
Respect. Heretofore,

08:29.709 --> 08:35.047
you can refer to me
as Stingray.

08:35.080 --> 08:37.116
Yeah, all right, Chubs.
He's in your team.

08:38.917 --> 08:40.086
Terrific.

08:45.090 --> 08:46.192
DANIEL: Two...

08:46.892 --> 08:48.561
[GRUNTING]

08:57.302 --> 08:58.204
Five.

08:58.904 --> 09:00.239
[GRUNTING]

09:01.640 --> 09:02.942
[CHUCKLES] Got you.

09:02.975 --> 09:05.011
All right, Demetri's turn.
Come on.

09:05.044 --> 09:06.913
Demetri, get in there.

09:08.214 --> 09:09.582
Set.

09:13.418 --> 09:14.520
Three.

09:14.553 --> 09:16.756
[DEMETRI WHIMPERS, GROANS]

09:16.789 --> 09:19.025
Sorry, Meat.
You gotta block that.

09:21.226 --> 09:22.595
Six.

09:23.762 --> 09:25.131
[DEMETRI GROANING]

09:26.198 --> 09:27.533
I hate this.

09:27.566 --> 09:29.968
All right, come on, get up.

09:30.002 --> 09:34.006
Can we please take a break?
This heat is brutal.

09:38.610 --> 09:40.046
You guys wanna cool off?

09:40.680 --> 09:41.814
ALL: Mmm-hmm.

09:41.847 --> 09:46.118
All right. I think I can
accommodate that.

09:46.151 --> 09:49.221
So, what happens
at the end of this
if it's just you and me?

09:49.255 --> 09:52.325
Then I guess I'll have to rip
that pretty little head band
off your head.

09:52.358 --> 09:55.227
Yeah, this headband
is staying right where it is.

09:55.260 --> 09:56.929
[RUSTLING]

09:58.564 --> 09:59.732
Oh, shit.

09:58.564 --> 09:59.732
[CHUCKLES]

10:01.467 --> 10:02.835
[EXHALES]

10:06.338 --> 10:07.940
[BOTH GRUNTING]

10:08.474 --> 10:09.742
[CHUCKLES]

10:10.309 --> 10:11.744
He's all yours.

10:11.777 --> 10:12.611
Nah.

10:12.644 --> 10:14.213
[BOTH GRUNTING]

10:14.714 --> 10:15.948
Ladies first.

10:19.284 --> 10:20.386
Thanks.

10:21.453 --> 10:22.755
[GROANS]

10:23.355 --> 10:24.623
No hard feelings.

10:24.657 --> 10:27.093
No mercy.

10:33.265 --> 10:36.068
So, you couldn't take
the heat of Shochu-Geiko,

10:36.101 --> 10:39.872
perhaps, you'll find
Kangeiko more to your liking.

10:39.905 --> 10:42.474
Are there are no "geikos"
that takes place in a spa?

10:42.507 --> 10:44.243
No, it's not about the heat
or the cold.

10:44.276 --> 10:46.544
It's about adapting
to the environment around you

10:46.578 --> 10:48.680
and using that
to your advantage.

10:48.714 --> 10:51.150
Look around,
what do you see?

10:51.183 --> 10:52.451
Frozen London broil.

10:52.484 --> 10:54.420
No, not the meat,
look past that.

10:55.754 --> 10:58.524
I see the exhalation of breath.

10:58.557 --> 11:01.293
The twitch of a muscle.

11:01.326 --> 11:03.095
The shift of a stance.

11:03.128 --> 11:06.565
If you lean into the cold,
it will heighten your senses.

11:06.599 --> 11:10.336
And then you'll anticipate
the moment before
your opponent strikes.

11:10.369 --> 11:12.337
And you'll always be ready.

11:12.371 --> 11:13.673
Yeah.

11:12.371 --> 11:13.673
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

11:19.578 --> 11:22.047
All right, circle up.

11:22.081 --> 11:24.083
[SOFT MUSIC
PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

11:26.318 --> 11:27.386
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

11:31.857 --> 11:33.659
Was that Daniel?

11:33.692 --> 11:35.728
Yeah, he's not coming.

11:40.232 --> 11:42.300
[LINE RINGING]

11:42.334 --> 11:43.936
[ON VOICEMAIL]
<i> Hey, you've reached
Daniel LaRusso.</i>

11:43.969 --> 11:46.305
<i> Sorry I can't come to the...</i>

11:43.969 --> 11:46.305
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

11:53.245 --> 11:54.413
[BIRD SCREECHING]

11:56.248 --> 11:57.416
[ELI YELLING]

12:01.587 --> 12:02.921
What the hell, man?

12:02.954 --> 12:05.791
Sorry, ass-face.
Today, you're the enemy.

12:05.824 --> 12:07.727
That makes five kills.

12:09.228 --> 12:12.231
Guess I earned
my Medal of Honor.

12:25.243 --> 12:26.779
Seven.

12:33.619 --> 12:34.987
[GRUNTING]

12:36.689 --> 12:38.157
DANIEL: That's what
I'm talking about.

12:41.226 --> 12:43.662
Five.

12:43.695 --> 12:44.930
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

12:53.205 --> 12:54.507
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:17.162 --> 13:19.198
All right. Let's get
Demetri in there.

13:19.631 --> 13:21.833
Good job.

13:21.867 --> 13:24.536
All right,
here goes nothing.

13:24.570 --> 13:26.304
Literally.

13:26.338 --> 13:27.873
Set.

13:28.206 --> 13:29.308
Six.

13:29.641 --> 13:31.109
[GROANS]

13:31.143 --> 13:34.012
Come on, Demetri.
Look for the signs.

13:34.045 --> 13:36.748
Anticipate, you can do this.
All right, focus.

13:36.782 --> 13:38.217
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

13:38.250 --> 13:39.217
Come on, Demetri.

13:39.251 --> 13:41.320
DEMETRI: Oh, you, come on.
Just give me a second.

13:43.788 --> 13:46.458
[INDISTINCT TALKING]

13:46.491 --> 13:49.428
It's all right, Miss Robinson,
you'll get them next time.

13:50.996 --> 13:52.698
They got you out, too?

13:52.731 --> 13:53.965
Yeah.

13:53.998 --> 13:56.402
I guess there's just
Hawk and Miguel left.

13:58.537 --> 14:00.472
I can't do it, Mr. LaRusso.

14:00.505 --> 14:05.243
Between the cold
and the shouting
and the hole in my sock...

14:05.276 --> 14:08.247
I'm not sure
when that happened,
but it's real uncomfortable.

14:08.280 --> 14:12.618
Demetri, you are the most
neurotic person that I know.

14:13.452 --> 14:15.321
You always expect the worst.

14:16.354 --> 14:19.525
But you could use that
to your advantage.

14:19.558 --> 14:21.660
It means you anticipate.

14:21.694 --> 14:23.395
Think of it like
a Spidey-Sense.

14:23.428 --> 14:26.365
Actually, in the comics,
they call it, "Spider-Sense."

14:26.398 --> 14:29.001
Look, Demetri, this isn't
about who's fastest

14:29.034 --> 14:31.970
and who's strongest.
This is about instincts.

14:32.004 --> 14:34.073
It's about using
what's in here.

14:34.673 --> 14:36.175
You think you could do that?

14:40.379 --> 14:41.746
All right.

14:41.780 --> 14:43.649
Let's try it again.

14:43.682 --> 14:47.319
Remember, anticipate.

14:54.392 --> 14:55.393
Two.

14:55.427 --> 14:56.462
[EXHALES]

15:04.469 --> 15:05.604
[GRUNTS]

15:09.741 --> 15:11.110
[YELLS]

15:09.741 --> 15:11.110
[STUDENTS EXCLAIM]

15:13.178 --> 15:14.245
Whoo!

15:14.279 --> 15:15.647
I did it!

15:15.680 --> 15:16.848
Five.

15:16.881 --> 15:18.817
[GROANING]

15:18.850 --> 15:21.019
Okay, that's okay.
Baby steps.

15:21.052 --> 15:23.622
Baby steps, right?

15:21.052 --> 15:23.622
Yeah. Mmm-hmm.

15:23.656 --> 15:24.890
Good job, bro.

15:24.923 --> 15:26.758
STUDENT 1: Good job.

15:24.923 --> 15:26.758
STUDENT 2: Nice.

15:26.792 --> 15:28.360
[STUDENTS CHATTERING EXCITEDLY]

15:29.494 --> 15:30.963
[DEMETRI CHUCKLES]

15:32.564 --> 15:33.932
Is everything okay, Dad?

15:33.965 --> 15:35.867
Yeah, yeah.

15:35.901 --> 15:37.202
Um, I'll meet you at home.

15:37.235 --> 15:38.803
That's all for today, guys.

15:38.837 --> 15:41.106
Great job.

15:42.741 --> 15:44.176
[BIRDS CAWING]

15:47.679 --> 15:49.315
Finally, a worthy opponent.

15:50.481 --> 15:54.420
So, you're the one
that trashed Miyagi-Do?

15:54.453 --> 15:56.888
They're the enemy.
I had to put them
in their place.

15:56.921 --> 16:01.026
So, that means you had to
trash their dojo, and steal
their Medal of Honor?

16:01.059 --> 16:02.661
What do you care?

16:02.695 --> 16:06.265
Just 'cause you still have
a thing for Sam doesn't mean
I have to go soft.

16:06.298 --> 16:09.301
I'm not soft.
And this isn't about her.

16:10.202 --> 16:13.405
Nah, sure it isn't.

16:14.973 --> 16:17.676
You want the medal so bad,
come and take it.

16:26.919 --> 16:28.454
[BOTH GRUNTING]

16:38.997 --> 16:40.164
[ELI SCREAMS]

16:40.198 --> 16:41.567
STUDENT:
Is that Miguel and Hawk?

16:46.037 --> 16:47.373
Is that all you got?

16:58.684 --> 16:59.785
[PANTING]

17:08.694 --> 17:10.329
That's all I've got.

17:17.869 --> 17:19.071
[GRUNTS]

17:20.905 --> 17:22.341
Finish him.

17:23.542 --> 17:24.643
[GRUNTING]

17:24.676 --> 17:25.711
[STUDENTS EXCLAIMING]

17:27.812 --> 17:28.980
Team Black!

17:29.013 --> 17:31.116
STUDENTS: [CHEERING]
Yeah!

17:37.956 --> 17:39.258
Looks like that champ of yours

17:39.291 --> 17:41.460
is developing
a real killer instinct.

17:44.963 --> 17:47.098
You know, the thing
about stingrays is,

17:47.132 --> 17:51.035
they lie in wait
for the perfect opportunity

17:51.069 --> 17:53.538
to strike!

17:53.571 --> 17:54.673
[GRUNTS]

17:55.840 --> 17:58.177
The red team just won!

17:58.210 --> 17:59.812
[NESTOR YELLING]

18:00.612 --> 18:02.548
Whoo! Yeah!

18:05.250 --> 18:07.185
Good work, Stingray.

18:07.218 --> 18:09.254
Thank you, Sensei.

18:10.656 --> 18:12.424
[ALL CHEERING]

18:14.192 --> 18:15.894
What was that?

18:15.928 --> 18:17.863
That's not how
I taught you to fight.

18:17.896 --> 18:19.664
It's what Sensei Kreese
taught us.

18:19.698 --> 18:21.834
This isn't a tournament,
this is real life.

18:23.201 --> 18:26.438
Is that how
you wanna live your life?

18:50.261 --> 18:53.297
I like what you've done
with the place.

18:53.331 --> 18:57.870
It's very "home dojo chic."

18:59.171 --> 19:00.472
[CHUCKLES]

19:00.505 --> 19:01.640
Thanks.

19:03.508 --> 19:05.711
So, what did you like
better today?

19:05.744 --> 19:06.912
The heat or the cold?

19:08.246 --> 19:10.649
You know, they both have
their pluses and minuses.

19:10.682 --> 19:16.488
But if I had to pick one,
I'd say room temp.

19:16.522 --> 19:17.623
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

19:17.656 --> 19:19.158
That wasn't an option.

19:22.227 --> 19:24.429
What about you?

19:29.901 --> 19:30.903
I like the heat.

19:35.841 --> 19:37.276
I thought we weren't.

19:39.878 --> 19:41.413
We weren't...

20:00.065 --> 20:01.900
AMANDA: He left.

20:03.134 --> 20:05.236
Oh, I was gonna
buy him surf n' turf

20:05.269 --> 20:06.671
at Delmonico's.
I'll call his cell.

20:06.705 --> 20:09.241
No, Daniel, he quit.

20:09.274 --> 20:11.643
Anoush gave his notice.

20:09.274 --> 20:11.643
What?

20:12.510 --> 20:14.479
Tom Cole offered him
a higher title.

20:14.513 --> 20:17.549
Better money.
He was gonna give us
a chance to match it,

20:17.582 --> 20:19.217
but then you bailed on him.

20:19.250 --> 20:22.588
Okay, I know, all right.
Listen, this is an easy fix.
I'll call Anoush

20:22.621 --> 20:25.490
and I'll clear it up.

20:22.621 --> 20:25.490
This isn't about Anoush.

20:25.523 --> 20:27.825
This is about you
not being able
to keep your promises.

20:27.859 --> 20:29.827
You said you would be able
to balance everything

20:29.861 --> 20:31.296
and now look where we are.

20:31.329 --> 20:34.232
Today got away from me, okay?
It's not gonna happen again,
I promise,

20:34.266 --> 20:35.400
I'll be
at the dealership more.

20:35.433 --> 20:36.935
[SCOFFS] You're not
getting it, Daniel.

20:36.968 --> 20:40.071
I'm not talking
about the dealership,
I'm talking about us.

20:40.105 --> 20:41.472
Ever since
you opened Miyagi-Do,

20:41.506 --> 20:43.241
I've been waking up
in an empty bed.

20:43.274 --> 20:45.310
I've been running
this business all by myself.

20:45.343 --> 20:49.548
I have spent the entire summer
feeling alone, while
you're off at karate camp.

20:50.782 --> 20:52.283
I'm sorry, okay?

20:52.317 --> 20:56.488
I've just been focused
on giving these kids
a chance to defend themselves.

20:57.689 --> 20:59.891
Well, sometimes,
when you focus on one thing,

20:59.925 --> 21:02.761
you lose focus of
everything else that matters.

21:19.077 --> 21:21.079
[CHUCKLING]

21:21.112 --> 21:22.648
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

21:24.249 --> 21:26.618
Sam, someone's at the door.

21:28.220 --> 21:29.755
Sam?

21:33.358 --> 21:35.427
What are you doing here?

21:33.358 --> 21:35.427
I'm not here to fight.

21:35.460 --> 21:38.696
I just came
to give something back.

21:38.730 --> 21:40.298
[SCOFFS]
I knew you took it.

21:40.331 --> 21:44.636
No, look, I had nothing
to do with that or
what happened to your dojo.

21:48.206 --> 21:49.875
We're not all assholes.

21:51.976 --> 21:54.880
Just tell Sam I said sorry.

22:08.093 --> 22:09.461
Who was that?

22:10.061 --> 22:12.431
Nobody. Had the wrong house.

22:12.797 --> 22:13.798
Weird.

22:13.831 --> 22:17.002
Well, I'm headed to bed.
It's been a day.

22:17.769 --> 22:20.439
Yeah. It has.

22:46.664 --> 22:47.666
Ah.

22:48.399 --> 22:49.667
Hey, Johnny.

22:49.700 --> 22:52.003
You come to congratulate me
on my victory?

22:53.071 --> 22:54.873
We need to talk.

22:54.906 --> 22:56.408
About what?

22:56.441 --> 22:59.845
About what you've been
putting in my kids' heads
since I've been gone.

22:59.878 --> 23:04.249
Well, just been teaching
them the way of the fist.

23:04.282 --> 23:05.684
The same lessons
I taught you.

23:06.318 --> 23:08.687
Strike first, strike hard.

23:09.320 --> 23:11.189
No mercy.

23:11.223 --> 23:13.125
Yeah, that's where
we have a problem.

23:14.091 --> 23:17.295
Oh, do we?

23:14.091 --> 23:17.295
Yeah.

23:17.328 --> 23:20.765
Cobra Kai needs to change.

23:20.799 --> 23:24.502
What you taught
didn't work back then,
and it doesn't work now.

23:24.536 --> 23:25.737
What, do you wanna
change it to,

23:25.770 --> 23:28.940
something nice and snuggly,
like a blanket?

23:28.974 --> 23:30.174
No.

23:30.208 --> 23:32.777
Cobra Kai will always
be badass.

23:32.810 --> 23:35.814
But there's a difference
between no mercy
and no honor.

23:35.847 --> 23:36.948
Ah...

23:37.682 --> 23:38.950
Honor?

23:43.488 --> 23:46.157
Let me tell you something.

23:46.190 --> 23:49.060
When you're in a war,

23:49.094 --> 23:52.831
the other side never fights
with any honor.

23:52.864 --> 23:55.667
Take it from me, I know.
Trust me, I've been there.

23:55.700 --> 23:57.635
Be glad
that you don't know.

23:57.669 --> 24:00.037
Yeah, I don't know what "shit"
you went through back then,

24:00.071 --> 24:03.841
but these are good kids,
and they don't need
to relive our mistakes.

24:03.874 --> 24:06.945
The only mistake
is teaching them weakness.

24:06.978 --> 24:10.181
Like what you did
when you backed down
from LaRusso's challenge.

24:10.215 --> 24:12.216
Is that what
the new Cobra Kai
is all about?

24:12.250 --> 24:14.719
If you're trying
to get me riled up,
it's not gonna work.

24:14.752 --> 24:16.587
I'm responsible
for these students.

24:16.621 --> 24:19.223
And I am responsible
for you.

24:19.257 --> 24:21.359
You are still my student.

24:21.392 --> 24:23.661
I'm worried
about you, Johnny.

24:23.695 --> 24:25.529
I see what's gonna happen.

24:25.563 --> 24:28.366
You're gonna
let your guard down.

24:28.400 --> 24:30.501
And that's gonna
leave you vulnerable.

24:30.534 --> 24:32.804
All right, maybe
that's what you think...

24:34.572 --> 24:36.708
But this is my dojo,

24:36.741 --> 24:38.876
and I make the rules.

24:38.910 --> 24:41.379
Your dojo?

24:41.413 --> 24:43.515
You forget
who started Cobra Kai?

24:43.548 --> 24:45.183
I haven't forgotten anything.

24:49.521 --> 24:52.090
You know what?

24:52.123 --> 24:55.526
I'm sorry.
I thought this could work,
but I was wrong.

24:55.559 --> 24:58.730
Look...

24:55.559 --> 24:58.730
We're done!

24:58.763 --> 25:04.236
I don't ever wanna
see you in this dojo again.

25:29.127 --> 25:30.562
[DOORBELL JINGLES]

25:41.139 --> 25:42.740
JOHNNY:<i> Today, we'll be
learning one of the most</i>

25:42.773 --> 25:44.976
important lessons
a Cobra Kai could know.

25:45.010 --> 25:46.678
MAN: Bugger off.

25:46.711 --> 25:48.346
JOHNNY:<i> Headbutting.</i>

25:48.379 --> 25:49.514
DANIEL:
<i> This is me trying to help.</i>

25:49.547 --> 25:50.915
What else can I do, Amanda?

25:50.948 --> 25:54.319
You might wanna work on that,
so, you can get off the couch.

25:54.352 --> 25:56.687
If you wanted to,
I could set you up
on an app.

25:56.721 --> 26:00.224
<i> That's how my mom
found her boyfriend.</i>

26:00.257 --> 26:03.027
MIGUEL:<i> If you like her,
just swipe right, and we'll
set up a bunch of dates.</i>

26:03.061 --> 26:05.596
WOMAN: We combat
all institutions of oppression.

26:05.629 --> 26:07.565
Climate change,
denial, the patriarchy.

26:07.598 --> 26:09.134
I hate the Patriots, too.
